{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782211197238,"sessionID":"ses_10bf585e9fferjmNcR8To5cw5o","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"call_c23ce98cddc2492b8713cbb0","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# Iteration 2: Security\n\n## Focus\nDimension: D2 Security\nFiles: frontmatter-version.mjs, check-frontmatter-versions.sh, quick_validate.py, package_skill.py\nScope: Path traversal, injection, env handling, unsafe deserialization, credential exposure\n\n## Scorecard\n- Dimensions covered: security\n- Files reviewed: 4\n- New findings: P0=0 P1=0 P2=1\n- Refined findings: P0=0 P1=0 P2=0\n- New findings ratio: 0.17\n\n## Findings\n\n### P0, Blocker\n_(none)_\n\n### P1, Required\n_(none)_\n\n### P2, Suggestion\n\n- **F006**: No explicit path boundary validation on file writes in frontmatter-version.mjs, `frontmatter-version.mjs:295`. The `applyVersion` function writes to `absFile` without checking that the path stays within the skills root directory. A caller passing `--paths` with a file containing absolute paths outside the skills tree could cause writes to arbitrary locations. Mitigated by: (1) the tool is a developer utility, not a network service; (2) `discoverInScope` constrains to the skills root; (3) the `--paths` flag reads from a file list that is typically generated by the tool itself. Low practical risk but worth a defensive check.\n\n```json\n{\n  \"findingId\": \"F006\",\n  \"claim\": \"applyVersion writes to absFile without checking that the path stays within the skills root, allowing potential writes outside scope via --paths flag.\",\n  \"evidenceRefs\": [\n    \"frontmatter-version.mjs:295\",\n    \"frontmatter-version.mjs:391-393\"\n  ],\n  \"counterevidenceSought\": \"Checked if --paths input is validated against skillsRoot. The discoverInScope function constrains to skills root, but --paths bypasses that. Checked if any caller passes untrusted paths — all known callers are the tool itself or test harnesses.\",\n  \"alternativeExplanation\": \"The tool is a developer utility meant to run in a trusted context. The --paths flag is a developer convenience, not an attack surface. The real protection is that the tool runs in a controlled dev environment.\",\n  \"finalSeverity\": \"P2\",\n  \"confidence\": 0.80,\n  \"downgradeTrigger\": \"If a path boundary assertion is added to applyVersion, this finding resolves.\",\n  \"transitions\": [\n    { \"iteration\": 2, \"from\": null, \"to\": \"P2\", \"reason\": \"Initial discovery — defensive boundary check missing\" }\n  ]\n}\n```\n\n## Cross-Reference Results\n| Protocol | Status | Gate | Evidence | Notes |\n|----------|--------|------|----------|-------|\n| spec_code | partial | hard | Scripts exist and match spec claims | No security-specific spec claims to verify |\n\n## Assessment\n- New findings ratio: 0.17 (1 P2 finding weighted at 1.0, total weighted 6.0 including prior P1 findings carried forward)\n- Dimensions addressed: [security]\n- Novelty justification: First security dimension pass; scripts are clean with only one minor advisory\n\n## Ruled Out\n- Shell injection via execFile: execFile uses array args, no shell interpolation — safe\n- YAML deserialization attacks: parseFrontmatter is line-wise regex, never uses a YAML parser — safe\n- Credential exposure: scripts handle no secrets, keys, or tokens\n\n## Dead Ends\n- Searched for env var handling: scripts use no env vars beyond standard git/PATH\n- Checked for eval/exec: none found in any script\n\n## Recommended Next Focus\n**D3 Traceability** — Verify spec claims against implementation, cross-reference integrity between parent and child specs, and checklist evidence.\n","filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-frontmatter-versioning/review/lineages/mimo/iterations/iteration-002.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-frontmatter-versioning/review/lineages/mimo/iterations/iteration-002.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-frontmatter-versioning/review/lineages/mimo/iterations/iteration-002.md","time":{"start":1782211197229,"end":1782211197236}},"id":"prt_ef410b928001pCrvPm2lGn1Zn4","sessionID":"ses_10bf585e9fferjmNcR8To5cw5o","messageID":"msg_ef4105906001wFhCDoIa5u7rjG"}}
