{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782211308752,"sessionID":"ses_10bf585e9fferjmNcR8To5cw5o","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"call_84bd30a7c9724cddb8badcca","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# Iteration 3: Traceability\n\n## Focus\nDimension: D3 Traceability\nFiles: spec.md (parent), all 5 child spec.md, all plan.md, all implementation-summary.md, description.json\nScope: Spec/code alignment, cross-reference integrity, checklist evidence, plan completeness\n\n## Scorecard\n- Dimensions covered: traceability\n- Files reviewed: 18\n- New findings: P0=0 P1=1 P2=2\n- Refined findings: P0=0 P1=0 P2=0\n- New findings ratio: 0.33\n\n## Findings\n\n### P0, Blocker\n_(none)_\n\n### P1, Required\n\n- **F007**: plan.md files are scaffold templates never updated to reflect actual implementation, `001-versioning-standard/plan.md:44-56`, `002-derivation-engine/plan.md:44-56`, `003-apply-core-skill-docs/plan.md`, `004-apply-catalogs-and-playbooks/plan.md`, `005-verify-and-enforce/plan.md:44-56`. All five phase `plan.md` files contain only placeholder content: `[2-3 sentences: what this implements and the technical approach]`, `[e.g., TypeScript, Python 3.11]`, `[MVC | MVVM | Clean Architecture | Serverless | Monolith | Other]`. The actual implementation details, architecture decisions, and technical approach are only documented in `implementation-summary.md`. Combined with F001 (tasks.md scaffolds), this means both the planning and task-tracking surfaces are stale scaffolds — the only completion evidence lives in implementation-summary.md files.\n\n```json\n{\n  \"findingId\": \"F007\",\n  \"claim\": \"All five phase plan.md files contain only generic scaffold template content with placeholder fields, creating a traceability gap alongside the stale tasks.md files (F001).\",\n  \"evidenceRefs\": [\n    \"001-versioning-standard/plan.md:44-56\",\n    \"002-derivation-engine/plan.md:44-56\"\n  ],\n  \"counterevidenceSought\": \"Checked all 5 plan.md files — all contain identical scaffold templates. No alternative planning document found. The implementation-summary.md files do contain architecture and decision records, but they are post-hoc summaries, not pre-implementation plans.\",\n  \"alternativeExplanation\": \"The implementation-summary.md may have been intended as the authoritative planning surface for this workflow, but the spec-kit contract expects plan.md to carry the pre-implementation plan.\",\n  \"finalSeverity\": \"P1\",\n  \"confidence\": 0.90,\n  \"downgradeTrigger\": \"If the spec-kit framework explicitly allows implementation-summary.md to serve as the plan surface, downgrade to P2.\",\n  \"transitions\": [\n    { \"iteration\": 3, \"from\": null, \"to\": \"P1\", \"reason\": \"Initial discovery — plan.md scaffolds parallel the tasks.md scaffolds (F001)\" }\n  ]\n}\n```\n\n### P2, Suggestion\n\n- **F008**: Parent spec says \"~436 core docs\" but Phase 3 actually versioned 457, `spec.md:103`. The parent spec's Files to Change table says \"~436 core docs\" but the Phase 3 implementation-summary reports 457 core docs versioned (422 fresh inserts + 23 already correct + 12 normalized). The 21-file discrepancy is a minor cross-reference inaccuracy between parent spec and child implementation.\n\n- **F009**: description.json has truncated description field, `description.json:4`. The description reads `Skill documentation (SKILL.md, README.md, references/.md, assets//.md, feature catalogs, testing playbooks) carries YAML frontmatter consumed` — it cuts off mid-sentence at \"consumed\". The full sentence should end with something like \"consumed by the skill advisor and system-spec-kit.\" This breaks any downstream consumer that reads the description for display or indexing.\n\n```json\n{\n  \"findingId\": \"F009\",\n  \"claim\": \"description.json description field is truncated mid-sentence at 'consumed', breaking downstream consumers that read it for display or indexing.\",\n  \"evidenceRefs\": [\n    \"description.json:4\"\n  ],\n  \"counterevidenceSought\": \"Checked if the truncation is intentional or a generation artifact. The spec.md:74 has the full sentence. The description.json was generated by generate-context.js. The truncation appears to be a generation bug (likely hitting a length limit).\",\n  \"alternativeExplanation\": \"Could be an intentional field length limit in the generate-context.js script, but the truncation mid-word suggests a bug rather than a policy.\",\n  \"finalSeverity\": \"P2\",\n  \"confidence\": 0.85,\n  \"downgradeTrigger\": \"If the description field is documented as having a character limit that causes this truncation, this is by design.\",\n  \"transitions\": [\n    { \"iteration\": 3, \"from\": null, \"to\": \"P2\", \"reason\": \"Initial discovery — truncated description in generated metadata\" }\n  ]\n}\n```\n\n## Cross-Reference Results\n| Protocol | Status | Gate | Evidence | Notes |\n|----------|--------|------|----------|-------|\n| spec_code | partial | hard | No code in spec folder; scripts exist in sk-doc | Spec-only packet |\n| checklist_evidence | fail | hard | No checklist.md exists | Level 2 requires checklist.md |\n\n## Assessment\n- New findings ratio: 0.33 (1 P1 at weight 5.0 + 2 P2 at weight 1.0 each = 7.0 new / 21.0 total)\n- Dimensions addressed: [traceability]\n- Novelty justification: plan.md scaffolds (F007) confirm the pattern from F001 (tasks.md scaffolds). description.json truncation (F009) is a new metadata bug.\n\n## Ruled Out\n- Spec claims vs implementation: All normative spec claims (4-part version, changelog-anchored derivation, numstat gate, idempotent insertion, enforcement gate) match the implementation\n\n## Dead Ends\n- Searched for checklist.md at all levels — none exist\n- Checked for alternative task-tracking surfaces — none found beyond implementation-summary.md\n\n## Recommended Next Focus\n**D4 Maintainability** — Review documentation quality, code patterns, and ease of follow-on changes across the spec folder.\n","filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-frontmatter-versioning/review/lineages/mimo/iterations/iteration-003.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-frontmatter-versioning/review/lineages/mimo/iterations/iteration-003.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-frontmatter-versioning/review/lineages/mimo/iterations/iteration-003.md","time":{"start":1782211308746,"end":1782211308750}},"id":"prt_ef4126cc7001kamGWUQ9r5QoMA","sessionID":"ses_10bf585e9fferjmNcR8To5cw5o","messageID":"msg_ef4120173001pbjzbXv5jdOJ0O"}}
